# Copy to .env (which is gitignored) for local `pnpm dev` and for `vercel dev` /
# `netlify dev`, and set the same vars in your Vercel/Netlify project environment
# for production. NEVER commit a real key — the serverless proxy is the only
# place it should live.

# Required: the AI copilot proxy (/api/chat) uses this.
# Get a FREE key (no billing) at: https://aistudio.google.com/apikey
GEMINI_API_KEY=your-gemini-key-here

# Optional: model for the copilot (default: gemini-2.5-flash).
# If you hit "quota: limit 0" on one model, try another: gemini-2.5-flash-lite
# (lightest free), gemini-2.0-flash. A limit:0 error usually means this KEY/
# PROJECT/REGION has no free quota — make a new key in a new project, or enable
# billing (paid tier still has a free monthly allowance).
# MODELVISIO_MODEL=gemini-2.5-flash

# Optional: Google Search grounding lets the copilot cite real, current links.
# Default: OFF on Netlify (its slow grounded call + cold start blows the hard 10s
# free-tier limit → 502), ON on Vercel (60s limit). Set "on" to force citations
# (best on a paid plan with a higher MODELVISIO_TIMEOUT_MS), or "off" to disable.
# MODELVISIO_WEB_SEARCH=off

# Optional: time budget (ms) for one chat turn. The proxy aborts and answers
# within this so the serverless platform never kills it with an opaque 502.
# Default 7000 on Netlify (hard 10s sync limit incl. cold start, free tier),
# 55000 on Vercel.
# MODELVISIO_TIMEOUT_MS=7000

# Optional: let gemini-2.5 models "think" before answering. OFF by default —
# thinking adds seconds and can exceed the Netlify free 10s limit. Turn on only
# if you raised MODELVISIO_TIMEOUT_MS on a plan with a longer function timeout.
# MODELVISIO_THINKING=off

# Optional: server-side usage logging to Supabase. When BOTH are set, the /api/chat
# proxy records model uploads and chat queries to your Supabase table (default:
# usage_logs). These live ONLY on the server — they are never sent to the browser,
# and the table uses RLS with no policies so only this service-role key can read it.
# Leave unset to disable logging entirely (the app behaves identically). Find these
# in Supabase → Project Settings → API. Use the SERVICE ROLE key (secret), NOT anon.
# SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
# SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key-here
# SUPABASE_LOG_TABLE=usage_logs
